  "description": "Music is organized sound — but organized by whom, for whom, and according to what principles? This lesson introduces the basic structural parameters of music (rhythm, melody, harmony, timbre) not as neutral, universal categories but as analytical tools with specific cultural origins and embedded assumptions.\n¶The parameters All musical traditions organize sound, but they do not all organize the same parameters in the same ways or with the same priorities.\n",
